        "root": {
            "text": "This week's code & coffee focus is on getting my little synth up and running so I can hook it into Orca & my live coding tool.  The lisp syntax is just an example of what I'm going for (the graph is currently hooked up in code using a similar set of api calls); I'm not sure on the best approach yet.  I've looked at 'Fe' as a simpler language I can play with more (currently I embed Chibi Scheme).  The synth is just a directed graph, but initially I want to just show a sensibly ordered list of nodes with buttons on them.  The live code workflow is something like:\n• Declare synth in code\n• Tweak synth through easy UI\n• Declare patterns\/whatever in code to drive it, or use Orca.",
